# Telemetry Directory

This directory stores entropy measurements and workflow telemetry.

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `runs.jsonl` | Each workflow execution |
| `entropy.jsonl` | Calculated entropy per run |
| `adjustments.jsonl` | Threshold/config changes |
| `events.jsonl` | High-entropy events |

## Format: runs.jsonl

```json
{"ts":1699999999,"workflow":"harvest","duration_s":42,"status":"success","entries":150}
{"ts":1700000000,"workflow":"process","duration_s":120,"status":"success","entries":150}
```

## Format: entropy.jsonl

```json
{"ts":1699999999,"workflow":"harvest","entropy":0.23,"outcomes":{"success":145,"partial":5,"failure":0}}
```

## Format: adjustments.jsonl

```json
{"ts":1699999999,"type":"threshold","field":"moisture","old":15,"new":18,"reason":"calibration"}
```

## Usage

```bash
# View entropy trend
just entropy

# Log a workflow run
just telemetry-log workflow=harvest status=success duration_s=42

# Check for high-entropy events
just telemetry-alerts
```
